### Adjusting the Channel Management Logic

1. **Reserved Channel Tracking**: You need a way to distinguish reserved channels from those automatically managed. This could be as simple as another data structure tracking which channels are reserved. A `std::set<int>` could efficiently serve this purpose, as it allows for quick lookups and insertions.

2. **Modify `onChannelFinish` Callback**: The callback should check if a channel is reserved before setting it free. If the channel is reserved, it should not automatically free the channel upon sound completion.

3. **Reserving and Releasing Channels**: Provide methods in `AudioManager` to reserve and release channels. When reserving, mark the channel as used and add it to the reserved channels set. When releasing, remove from the reserved set and mark the channel as unused.

Here are the modifications to incorporate these ideas:

### AudioManager Adjustments

```cpp
class AudioManager
{
    public:
        // Existing functionality...

        int ReserveChannel();
        void ReleaseChannel(int channel);

    private:
        AudioManager();
        ~AudioManager();
        // Other members...

        std::vector<bool> channelsUsage; // Existing channel usage tracking
        std::set<int> reservedChannels; // New! Track reserved channels

        static void onChannelFinish(int channel); // Existing callback - adjust its logic

        // Helper methods...
};

AudioManager::AudioManager() {
    // Initialization...
    Mix_ChannelFinished(AudioManager::onChannelFinish);
}

void AudioManager::onChannelFinish(int channel) {
    if (GetInstance().reservedChannels.find(channel) == GetInstance().reservedChannels.end()) {
        // Channel is not reserved, set it free
        GetInstance().setChannelUsage(channel, false);
    }
    // If channel is reserved, do nothing - it stays reserved
}

int AudioManager::ReserveChannel() {
    int channel = getNextFreeChannel();
    if (channel != -1) {
        setChannelUsage(channel, true);
        reservedChannels.insert(channel); // Mark as reserved
    }
    return channel;
}

void AudioManager::ReleaseChannel(int channel) {
    if (reservedChannels.find(channel) != reservedChannels.end()) {
        reservedChannels.erase(channel); // Remove from reserved set
        setChannelUsage(channel, false);  // Mark as free again
    }
}
```

